         <abstract>
            <p>A rank-2 lattice rule is a quadrature rule for the (unit) $s$-dimensional hypercube, of the form $$Qf = (1/n_1n_2) \sum^{n_1}_{j_1 = 1} \sum^{n_2}_{j_2 = 1} \bar f(j_1\mathbf{z}_1/n_1 + j_2\mathbf{z}_2/n_2),$$ which cannot be re-expressed in an analogous form with a single sum. Here $\bar f$ is a periodic extension of $f$, and $\mathbf{z}_1, \mathbf{z}_2$ are integer vectors. In this paper we discuss these rules in detail; in particular, we categorize a special subclass, whose leading one- and two-dimensional projections contain the maximum feasible number of abscissas. We show that rules of this subclass can be expressed uniquely in a simple tricycle form.</p>
          </abstract>
